A simple ray tracer

* How to run:
First use command "make" to compile the code. Then use command "./raycast [–u | –d] step_max <options>" to run the program. User can press 'q' key to terminate the program. User can press 's' key to save the image. 

* Parameters:
option "-d" shows the default scene. option "-u" shows the user defined scene. “step_max" specifies the number of recursion levels for reflection and refraction.

* Options:
"+s": inclusion of shadows; ”+l": inclusion of reflection; “+r": inclusion of refraction; “+c": inclusion of chess board pattern; “+f": enabling diffuse rendering using stochastic ray generation; “+p": enabling super-sampling.
